\begin_layout Definition
In the normal form game where the 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 player set is 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

, the strategy profile 
\begin_inset Formula $(s_{1}^{*},...,s_{I}^{*})$
\end_inset

 is a NE if, for each player 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

, her strategy 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{i}^{*}$
\end_inset

 is a best response to the strategies specified for the other 
\begin_inset Formula $n-1$
\end_inset

 players, or for 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{s}_{-i}=(s_{1}^{*},...,s_{i-1}^{*},s_{i+1}^{*},...,s_{I}^{*})$
\end_inset

.
 Formally, 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray*}
u_{i}(s_{i}^{*},\vec{s}_{-i}) & \geq & u_{i}(s'_{i},\vec{s}_{-i}),\,\forall i,\,\forall s'_{i}\in S_{i},\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset

or
\end_layout

