\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{A}\subset\mathbb{R}^{n}$
\end_inset

 is a nonempty compact, convex set, and that 
\begin_inset Formula $f:\mathbb{A}\rightarrow\mathbb{A}$
\end_inset

 is an upper hemi-continuous correspondence from 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{A}$
\end_inset

 unto itself with the property that the set 
\begin_inset Formula $f(\vec{x})\subset\mathbb{A}$
\end_inset

 is nonempty and convex for every 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in\mathbb{A}$
\end_inset

.
